24
00:05:39,598 --> 00:05:43,209
450,000 square 
meters in total area.

25
00:05:43,209 --> 00:05:47,810
That and the artificial island off the coast 
of Kawasaki are the key points of this project.

26
00:05:47,810 --> 00:05:51,000
When it's done,
 the project will be in its final stage.

27
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:56,209
Then we'll construct a 15 km long dike 
to connect both islands to each other...

28
00:05:56,209 --> 00:06:00,019
...and to Kawasaki and 
Kisarazu on the mainland.

29
00:06:00,019 --> 00:06:05,019
When the project is complete it will not only 
provide a highway that circumvents the metropolis...

30
00:06:05,019 --> 00:06:09,329
...but it'll use tidal height differences 
to drain the water from the area.

31
00:06:09,329 --> 00:06:15,629
In ten years it'll have created 45,
000 hectares of new land.

32
00:06:15,629 --> 00:06:21,939
Enough to eliminate our land 
problems for the rest of the century.

33
00:06:21,939 --> 00:06:28,639
Like Babylon,
 Tokyo will be an eternal paradise.

34
00:06:28,639 --> 00:06:31,038
Project Babylon...
 the biggest project of the century.

35
00:06:31,038 --> 00:06:35,750
Given the difficulty of the 
adjustments facing the participants...

36
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:39,949
...it might not've been completed in this century.
 But Labor systems made it possible.

37
00:06:39,949 --> 00:06:43,348
The basic research was 
completed in the late 80's.

38
00:06:43,348 --> 00:06:46,658
But if it weren't for the massive 
demand for this project...

39
00:06:46,658 --> 00:06:51,259
...it would never have 
developed this quickly.

40
00:06:51,259 --> 00:06:57,468
As a matter of fact, we have a total of 
3600 Labors working here, large and small.

41
00:06:57,468 --> 00:07:02,670
That's about 40% of the Labors 
working in the entire country.

42
00:07:02,670 --> 00:07:07,968
A Labor is a machine that can do 
the work of ten men in less time...

43
00:07:07,968 --> 00:07:11,180
...and this ocean project is only practical 
because of an intensive use of them.

44
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:14,778
An old fairytale 
is now coming true.

45
00:07:16,778 --> 00:07:20,879
Mind you... we're now getting 
things like Labor-crimes...

46
00:07:20,879 --> 00:07:23,189
...which we couldn't 
have imagined either.

47
00:07:23,189 --> 00:07:26,490
Aaahh, that's your 
specialty isn't it ?

48
00:07:33,088 --> 00:07:36,399
Oh,
 there it is at 5 o'clock.

49
00:07:36,399 --> 00:07:40,098
It's 500 meters in length,
  and 150 meters high.

50
00:07:40,098 --> 00:07:44,399
The platform handles maintenance for 
all the Labors working on the project.

51
00:07:44,399 --> 00:07:47,699
We call it the Ark

52
00:07:48,810 --> 00:07:51,408
Tell me...
 why's it called the Ark ?

53
00:07:51,408 --> 00:07:52,939
How the hell should l know ?

54
00:07:57,699 --> 00:08:01,120
Deactivating systems 1 to 5.

55
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,920
Display functioning normally...

56
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:05,620
See ?
 It's working perfectly.

57
00:08:05,620 --> 00:08:07,718
There don't seem to 
be any problems yet.

58
00:08:07,718 --> 00:08:10,620
Come on !
 There won't be any problems !

59
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:14,228
To begin with, we checked thoroughly 
before we even brought it in here.

60
00:08:14,228 --> 00:08:16,228
Was it Shige,
 from your place ?

61
00:08:16,228 --> 00:08:18,930
It's good to be careful,
 but he's too careful.

62
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:23,028
Anyway, there haven't been any 
problems with them, right ?

63
00:08:23,028 --> 00:08:25,639
The guys from Hachiouji have 
been pushing me to get the OK...

64
00:08:25,639 --> 00:08:28,338
...to roll out Unit #2 and 
start production of the others.

65
00:08:28,338 --> 00:08:31,639
...I'll start it up with 
the backup this time...

66
00:08:31,639 --> 00:08:32,839
Oh, wait.

67
00:08:32,839 --> 00:08:37,150
Two people from the second 
unit are here to pick you up.

68
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:39,450
The Second Unit ?

69
00:08:43,550 --> 00:08:44,950
...ALRIGHT !!!

70
00:08:44,950 --> 00:08:49,060
Whaddya think Noa ?
 Wasn't it worth coming over ?

71
00:08:49,060 --> 00:08:52,450
I don't like this kid...

72
00:08:52,450 --> 00:08:54,060
WHAT ?!

73
00:08:54,060 --> 00:08:57,160
You said you wanted to see it,
 so l made all the excuses to get here.

74
00:08:57,160 --> 00:08:58,259
And this's the thanks l get ?!

75
00:08:58,259 --> 00:09:00,060
Sorry,
 it just slipped out...

76
00:09:00,060 --> 00:09:01,869
Okay,
 let's call it a day.

77
00:09:01,869 --> 00:09:03,270
Roger

78
00:09:12,879 --> 00:09:14,579
Officers Shinohara 
and Izumi reporting.

79
00:09:14,579 --> 00:09:16,879
Here to pick up Chief Nagumo.

80
00:09:16,879 --> 00:09:18,180
Well,
 that was pretty quick.

81
00:09:18,180 --> 00:09:21,070
I didn't know you 
two were coming.

82
00:09:21,070 --> 00:09:25,190
We hitched a ride on a civilian chopper 
that happened to drop by SV2, Ma'am.

83
00:09:25,190 --> 00:09:28,890
The maintenance squad's 
ferry is on the way.

84
00:09:28,890 --> 00:09:32,989
But if possible, while we wait for it.
..I was wondering...

85
00:09:32,989 --> 00:09:35,089
You're Goto's men alright.

86
00:09:35,089 --> 00:09:38,099
I don't know how you 
sniffed it out...

87
00:09:38,099 --> 00:09:40,489
...but you can 
test it if you like.

88
00:09:40,489 --> 00:09:43,599
Though, Officer lzumi 
doesn't seem to like it...

89
00:09:43,599 --> 00:09:44,800
Looks like she heard us...

90
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:47,190
That's 'cause you didn't 
watch what you were saying.

91
00:09:47,190 --> 00:09:49,300
Now she'll have it in for you.

92
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:51,109
But what l said was true.

93
00:09:51,109 --> 00:09:53,609
He looks a bit villainous.

94
00:09:53,609 --> 00:09:55,609
That's a matter of opinion.

95
00:09:55,999 --> 00:09:58,609
Once it's officially registered 
it'll be called a Type-0...

96
00:09:58,609 --> 00:10:00,540
...the final version 
of the Type-98.

97
00:10:00,540 --> 00:10:06,520
It's also the first designed 
to be run entirely by HOS.

98
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:07,719
What's HOS ?

99
00:10:07,719 --> 00:10:11,520
You don't know a thing 
about software do you ?

100
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:15,930
It's a system program that makes 
Labors run more efficiently.

101
00:10:15,930 --> 00:10:17,829
Oh, it's just the 
Operating System...

102
00:10:17,829 --> 00:10:22,629
HOS is the revolutionary OS that 
Shinohara released two months ago.

103
00:10:22,629 --> 00:10:28,339
Even when installed in a conventional 
Labor it increases performance by 30%.

104
00:10:28,339 --> 00:10:31,640
Hyper Operating System,
 ``HOS''.

105
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:34,940
Most Labors now have their 
mainframes re-written to HOS.

106
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:38,239
But no matter how good the vehicle is,
 it all comes down to the pilot's...

107
00:10:38,239 --> 00:10:39,550
...
brains and guts !

108
00:10:39,550 --> 00:10:40,450
Good !

109
00:10:40,450 --> 00:10:44,650
Chief Nagumo of SV2,
 your ferry has arrived.

110
00:10:44,650 --> 00:10:46,749
Please go to deck A-12.

111
00:10:46,749 --> 00:10:47,749
WHAT ?!

112
00:10:47,749 --> 00:10:49,249
It's here already ?

113
00:10:49,249 --> 00:10:52,259
Come on,
 let's go.

114
00:11:03,869 --> 00:11:05,060
Wow !

115
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:07,060
Just like a world for giants !

116
00:11:07,060 --> 00:11:10,060
It's all Labor sized...

117
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:13,060
I'm gonna leave you two 
behind if you don't hurry !

118
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:14,869
Okay...!

119
00:11:21,070 --> 00:11:24,379
Chief Nagumo,
 can l ask you a question ?

120
00:11:24,379 --> 00:11:27,379
If it's about this place,
 l doubt l know any more than you...

121
00:11:27,379 --> 00:11:30,390
No,
 it's about the Type-0...

122
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:33,089
Why is it here ?

123
00:11:33,089 --> 00:11:36,790
You know that three 
of them were issued...

124
00:11:36,790 --> 00:11:40,190
...to the New York 
police as an experiment...

125
00:11:40,190 --> 00:11:42,339
You mean that crazy 
story about Kanuka...

126
00:11:42,339 --> 00:11:44,800
...becoming chief of the 
first Labor unit over there ?

127
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:48,489
Shige, who went over there to 
give technical assistance...

128
00:11:48,489 --> 00:11:53,109
...phoned me and asked if we could have it 
checked inside and out by someone from SV2.

129
00:11:53,109 --> 00:11:55,499
Well, here we have access to 
Shinohara's Labor facilities...

130
00:11:55,499 --> 00:11:57,499
...and we're close to the 
second command station.

131
00:11:57,499 --> 00:11:59,700
It's the perfect place 
to keep it secret.

132
00:11:59,700 --> 00:12:01,410
Is there a problem then ?

133
00:12:01,410 --> 00:12:02,700
Certainly not.

134
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:05,520
If there was, it would've 
caused big trouble already.

135
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:10,719
It's just that it was Shige who asked,
 so l couldn't ignore it.

136
00:12:22,629 --> 00:12:25,030
Extension of the 
training period ?

137
00:12:25,030 --> 00:12:28,930
But l had your word that we'd 
have everybody back this week !

138
00:12:28,930 --> 00:12:30,640
Yes,
 but things have changed.

139
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:38,140
The First unit's training on the Type-0 
is being extended for another week.

140
00:12:38,140 --> 00:12:40,739
I demand a complete explanation.

141
00:12:40,739 --> 00:12:44,550
We're already overworking the Second Unit,
 and they have problems to begin with.

142
00:12:44,550 --> 00:12:48,349
If we have to work them even harder,
 there's no telling what kind of disaster we could have.

143
00:12:48,349 --> 00:12:53,650
And I'm sure if we brought back the 
First Unit now they'd do just fine.

144
00:12:53,650 --> 00:12:56,759
Nagumo, this decision came 
from the main department.

145
00:12:56,759 --> 00:12:58,959
There's nothing l can do.

146
00:12:58,959 --> 00:13:01,759
Then I'll report to the 
main department myself...

147
00:13:01,759 --> 00:13:06,160
...and l will personally ask the Guard 
Division Chief to return the First Unit.

148
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,060
Wait !

149
00:13:09,369 --> 00:13:11,670
Look, this goes against 
my better judgement...

150
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:13,869
...
so try to keep it a secret.

151
00:13:13,869 --> 00:13:15,869
In the early morning,
 the day before yesterday...

152
00:13:15,869 --> 00:13:21,479
...the JSDF 7th Sector's prototype heavy Labor 
suddenly ran away during a wind tunnel test.

153
00:13:21,479 --> 00:13:25,180
It escaped from the base, and it actually 
took the paratroop Labor unit to stop it.

154
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:30,070
They don't know what caused 
the prototype to run away...

155
00:13:30,070 --> 00:13:32,290
...and it was so heavily damaged 
that examinations haven't helped.

156
00:13:32,290 --> 00:13:35,890
They must've been really panicked to have 
trashed it instead of taking it in one piece.

157
00:13:35,890 --> 00:13:38,489
But what does that 
have to do with this ?

158
00:13:38,489 --> 00:13:42,190
The Labor in question was built 
by Shinohara Heavy Industries...

159
00:13:42,190 --> 00:13:46,300
...and it had the 
same OS as the Type-0.

160
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:51,489
I should also mention that they're 
trying to cover up the fact...

161
00:13:51,489 --> 00:13:54,489
...that, at the time it ran away,
 he Labor was unmanned.

162
00:13:54,489 --> 00:13:58,209
You get the picture ?
 This could become a real problem.

163
00:13:58,410 --> 00:14:02,499
We'll have to practice self-restraint,
 as of right now.

164
00:14:02,499 --> 00:14:04,700
You're joking,
 right ?

165
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:06,609
Seriously ?

166
00:14:06,609 --> 00:14:10,920
Darn it.
 I hope this'll be over soon.

167
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:13,209
That's a rotten attitude !

168
00:14:13,209 --> 00:14:15,619
Until the First 
Unit comes back...

169
00:14:15,619 --> 00:14:19,420
...we're the only ones who can 
protect this city from criminals !

170
00:14:19,420 --> 00:14:22,530
And who's gonna protect 
our human rights ?

171
00:14:22,530 --> 00:14:23,829
We don't have any !!

172
00:14:23,829 --> 00:14:25,729
Shocking,
 isn't it Shinshi ?

173
00:14:25,729 --> 00:14:28,629
Yeah...I've only been home 
three times this month.

174
00:14:28,629 --> 00:14:31,329
It's a certified 
marriage crisis.

175
00:14:31,329 --> 00:14:34,040
That's why you shouldn't 
have gotten married !

176
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:36,540
Stationed in the middle of the reclaimed lands,
 far away from your family...

177
00:14:36,540 --> 00:14:41,040
But hey, aren't we getting 
more dispatches these days ?

178
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,440
Call from sector 7,
 205 at Shimoya, Taitoh Ward !

179
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:44,839
Second Unit report to the site !

180
00:14:44,839 --> 00:14:48,650
Repeat, 205 at Shimoya,
 Taitoh Ward...

181
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:50,650
As soon as you said it.
 Damn...

182
00:14:50,650 --> 00:14:52,450
Let's Go !!

183
00:14:52,450 --> 00:14:53,950
Roll out the trailer !

184
00:14:53,950 --> 00:14:56,349
Hurry up with that 
revolver cannon !

185
00:14:56,349 --> 00:14:59,359
I'll personally murder any 
slow-pokes, so move it !

186
00:15:04,759 --> 00:15:08,759
A dangerous Labor is out of 
control and moving this way !

187
00:15:08,759 --> 00:15:12,770
Please evacuate the area !

188
00:15:12,770 --> 00:15:15,670
Run !!

189
00:15:15,670 --> 00:15:20,770
Didn't you hear me ? I said run !
 Oh, here it comes !!

190
00:15:25,780 --> 00:15:30,579
This is Sakura Fubuki 12 to 
Chief Goto of SV2, Second Unit.

191
00:15:30,579 --> 00:15:35,589
The target's a Yotsubishi Tyrant 2000,
 from a construction site on Kokusai Street.

192
00:15:35,589 --> 00:15:41,190
It's moving at 4km an hour and 
destroying civilian buildings.

193
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:46,190
Shinohara, keep going along the 
river; try to get ahead of the Labor.

194
00:15:46,190 --> 00:15:46,999
Yes, sir !

195
00:15:46,999 --> 00:15:49,900
Unit #2, start up immediately 
and pursue the target.

196
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:51,300
Roger !

197
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:52,489
Beginning start-up.

198
00:15:52,489 --> 00:15:57,300
Ohta, remember ! Think of the driver's 
safety first ! You know what l mean ! !

199
00:15:57,300 --> 00:16:00,609
Shut Up ! Quick response !
 Believe in your judgement at the scene !

200
00:16:00,609 --> 00:16:04,609
Wouldn't it be better if you just 
said it out loud ? `DON'T USE THE GUN.'

201
00:16:04,609 --> 00:16:06,700
Raise him...

202
00:16:26,229 --> 00:16:30,129
The Yotsuboshi Tyrant is 
one of those heavy classes.

203
00:16:30,129 --> 00:16:33,729
It's not very fast, but it's guaranteed 
to have a lot of power. Watch it.

204
00:16:33,729 --> 00:16:37,140
I don't like these...

205
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:40,540
Hey !

206
00:16:40,540 --> 00:16:41,739
He went that way !

207
00:16:41,739 --> 00:16:43,940
That bastard crushed 
my squad car !

208
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:45,239
Make him pay !

209
00:16:45,239 --> 00:16:46,940
Leave it to me !

210
00:16:49,749 --> 00:16:52,749
YOU MORON !
 I HOPE YOU DROP DEAD !

211
00:16:56,349 --> 00:17:00,450
Somebody !
 Help me !

212
00:17:00,450 --> 00:17:04,259
You !
 Driving the Labor !

213
00:17:04,259 --> 00:17:07,959
This is the SV2, Second Unit !
 Hang on, l'm here to rescue you !

214
00:17:07,959 --> 00:17:10,558
SECOND UNlT ?
 I'm dead !

215
00:17:10,558 --> 00:17:11,558
What the...?!

216
00:17:11,558 --> 00:17:14,670
I was being nice to you,
 just because you're a tax payer !

217
00:17:14,670 --> 00:17:16,269
Well, no more Mr.
 Nice guy !

218
00:17:16,269 --> 00:17:19,058
You bastard !

219
00:17:24,370 --> 00:17:27,479
This is Sakura Fubuki 12,
 observing for Chief Goto.

220
00:17:27,479 --> 00:17:32,278
102 is pummeling the runaway Labor 
in the middle of a residential area.

221
00:17:32,278 --> 00:17:34,680
Oh,
 now it's kicking...

222
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:36,380
...
a drop kick now...

223
00:17:36,380 --> 00:17:39,989
Can't you do 
something about him ?

224
00:17:42,989 --> 00:17:44,190
Target and Unit #2 closing in.

225
00:17:44,190 --> 00:17:46,989
It's coming Noa !

226
00:17:46,989 --> 00:17:49,690
Hey, do something 
about the driver !

227
00:17:49,690 --> 00:17:53,190
This thing's too strong !

228
00:17:57,400 --> 00:18:00,298
Ohta !
 Use the stun stick !

229
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:05,308
Hit the S-RAM unit in the left chest 
area; you can finish it with one shot !

230
00:18:05,308 --> 00:18:07,308
Alright, done !

231
00:18:07,999 --> 00:18:11,700
Let's go grab some lunch.

232
00:18:12,910 --> 00:18:14,209
WHAT ?!

233
00:18:15,209 --> 00:18:17,719
What the hell !?

234
00:18:31,028 --> 00:18:33,729
Ohta, don't !

235
00:18:33,729 --> 00:18:36,430
All trailers,
 prepare to move out.

236
00:18:36,430 --> 00:18:40,038
You just bought the farm !

237
00:18:46,340 --> 00:18:47,640
Mission complete.

238
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:53,048
Target has been completely destroyed,
 damage to surrounding area extensive.

239
00:18:57,048 --> 00:19:01,749
Give it a careful washing,
 then dry it !

240
00:19:01,749 --> 00:19:02,450
Okay.

241
00:19:02,450 --> 00:19:05,058
And where's the twit who dropped 
the Labor into the river ?!

242
00:19:05,058 --> 00:19:06,759
He's taking a bath out back.

243
00:19:06,759 --> 00:19:08,759
Okay, tell him to report 
to me when he's done.

244
00:19:08,759 --> 00:19:09,759
Yes sir.

245
00:19:09,759 --> 00:19:11,660
Reactivated ?

246
00:19:11,660 --> 00:19:15,860
You mean to tell me that a 
deactivated Labor started up again...

247
00:19:15,860 --> 00:19:18,370
...
without a driver ?

248
00:19:18,370 --> 00:19:22,058
I couldn't believe it myself,
 even though l saw it with my own eyes.

249
00:19:22,058 --> 00:19:25,568
And that idiot filled it with so many 
holes there's nothing left to examine.

250
00:19:25,568 --> 00:19:27,269
Could you have made a mistake ?

251
00:19:27,269 --> 00:19:30,278
You guys are tired,
 you've had a lot of dispatches...

252
00:19:30,278 --> 00:19:32,580
What caused the 
original problem ?

253
00:19:32,580 --> 00:19:33,979
What did the 
driver have to say ?

254
00:19:33,979 --> 00:19:35,479
The usual sort of thing.

255
00:19:35,479 --> 00:19:38,580
It just started-up all 
of a sudden during work...

256
00:19:38,580 --> 00:19:40,180
Sure,
 of course he said that.

257
00:19:40,180 --> 00:19:42,090
After all,
 he caused one hell of a mess.

258
00:19:42,090 --> 00:19:44,090
But don't you think 
it's kind of unnatural ?

259
00:19:44,090 --> 00:19:46,288
Until two months ago nothing 
like this ever happened.

260
00:19:46,288 --> 00:19:48,890
We have 22 cases 
so far this month.

261
00:19:48,890 --> 00:19:52,390
I wish we could run away.

262
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:56,100
What do we do with this report ?

263
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,900
What do YOU do ?

264
00:19:57,900 --> 00:20:01,190
Do you think the brass 
would accept this ?

265
00:20:01,190 --> 00:20:04,190
As far as they're concerned,
 today's Labors can't possibly run away.

266
00:20:04,190 --> 00:20:07,110
Program malfunctions couldn't 
cause this kind of accident.

267
00:20:07,110 --> 00:20:10,110
We'll just have to 
settle for driver error.

268
00:20:10,110 --> 00:20:14,410
There won't be any 
legal action...

269
00:20:14,410 --> 00:20:17,700
...not when all they have is 
the testimony of the driver...

270
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:20,420
...and a black-listed 
Labor unit member.

271
00:20:23,620 --> 00:20:25,209
Noa !

272
00:20:25,209 --> 00:20:26,519
What is it ?

273
00:20:26,519 --> 00:20:28,920
Im not giving you any !
 This is my last bag !

274
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:32,830
Can you dig out the dispatch 
records for this month...

275
00:20:32,830 --> 00:20:33,729
...
and copies of the reports ?

276
00:20:33,729 --> 00:20:35,930
What do you want those for ?

277
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:38,028
Just do it.

278
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:39,630
Hey Pops !!

279
00:20:39,630 --> 00:20:41,330
Can l use the fridge ?!

280
00:20:41,330 --> 00:20:43,140
The computer room ?

281
00:20:45,640 --> 00:20:46,340
Alright.
 Go ahead.

282
00:20:46,340 --> 00:20:48,739
Thank-you !

283
00:20:48,739 --> 00:20:51,940
You're so good at using people.

284
00:20:51,940 --> 00:20:53,640
This isn't any of 
your business is it ?

285
00:20:53,640 --> 00:20:55,249
What's it got to 
do with the Type-0 ?

286
00:20:55,249 --> 00:20:59,048
Chief ! There's a call for you from 
Matsui of the lnvestigation division !

287
00:20:59,048 --> 00:21:01,450
Fine !
 I'll take it in my office.

288
00:21:01,450 --> 00:21:02,950
What have you started ?

289
00:21:02,950 --> 00:21:04,950
Why ?
 Interested ?

290
00:22:33,120 --> 00:22:36,930
``Yes. Shige Shiba from 
Tokyo City Police.''

291
00:22:36,930 --> 00:22:40,729
``Special Vehicle,
 Section #2.''

292
00:22:40,729 --> 00:22:42,028
``Absent ?''

293
00:22:42,028 --> 00:22:44,130
``Oh yeah,
 Kanuka Clancy.''

294
00:22:44,130 --> 00:22:45,630
Yes...

295
00:22:53,940 --> 00:22:55,739
Are you still at it ?

296
00:22:55,739 --> 00:22:58,749
Is that you Noa ? Don't stay in here,
 you might catch a cold.

297
00:22:58,749 --> 00:23:00,249
Go get some sleep.

298
00:23:00,249 --> 00:23:03,350
You never know when 
you'll get a dispatch.

299
00:23:03,350 --> 00:23:04,850
Right...

300
00:23:04,850 --> 00:23:07,048
You too, Asuma.

301
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:26,670
Wow !

302
00:23:26,670 --> 00:23:28,568
They're smaller than usual.

303
00:23:28,568 --> 00:23:30,269
I wasn't able to give them 
all the attention they needed.

304
00:23:30,269 --> 00:23:32,370
You're good at this,
 Hiromi.

305
00:23:32,370 --> 00:23:34,058
Everyone'll be so pleased.

306
00:23:34,058 --> 00:23:36,068
Well then, lzumi,
 please pick some.

307
00:23:36,068 --> 00:23:39,068
We aren't sending them to market,
 so just take the red, ripe ones.

308
00:23:39,068 --> 00:23:40,278
Okay...

309
00:23:40,278 --> 00:23:42,580
By the way,
 where's Asuma ?

310
00:23:42,580 --> 00:23:44,880
I thought he said he'd help,
 too.

311
00:23:44,880 --> 00:23:47,278
He said he was on his way 
to the chief's office.

312
00:23:47,278 --> 00:23:51,590
Looked like he'd pulled an all-nighter.
 It may have something to do with that...

313
00:23:51,590 --> 00:23:53,288
Hmmm.

314
00:23:55,489 --> 00:23:59,989
Hey, why don't we go share 
these with the chief ?

315
00:23:59,989 --> 00:24:05,600
Taking into consideration each 
Labor's manufacturer, condition...

316
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:11,400
...and the background of each driver,
 l've found only one common factor among the runaways.

317
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:16,999
All of them, regardless of manufacturer,
 have a Shinohara HOS mainframe.

318
00:24:16,999 --> 00:24:21,700
But 80% of registered 
Labors carry HOS...

319
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:24,410
Maybe, but it was in 
100% of the runaways.

320
00:24:24,410 --> 00:24:27,420
And another thing; the increase in 
runaway cases began two months ago...

321
00:24:27,420 --> 00:24:30,019
...coinciding with the 
date HOS was released.

322
00:24:30,019 --> 00:24:36,019
It can't be a coincidence.
 ``HOS'' has some fatal defect.

323
00:24:36,019 --> 00:24:38,830
I think we should submit this 
data to the department chiefs...

324
00:24:38,830 --> 00:24:44,130
...and press Shinohara to 
release the HOS program !

325
00:24:46,028 --> 00:24:47,229
Chief ?!

326
00:24:47,229 --> 00:24:52,440
HOS is a revolutionary OS,
 and it has monopolized the field.

327
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:57,940
If there should be any defect,
 it would ruin Shinohara.

328
00:24:57,940 --> 00:25:03,548
Besides, the officials who approve 
Labor OS's aren't total fools either.

329
00:25:03,548 --> 00:25:08,048
If there was any defect in HOS,
 it should have been detected during de-bug.

330
00:25:08,048 --> 00:25:08,850
But...!

331
00:25:08,850 --> 00:25:10,650
Listen.

332
00:25:10,650 --> 00:25:16,259
Let's say there is some relationship 
between the runaways and HOS.

333
00:25:16,259 --> 00:25:20,558
But what if ``HOS'' 
isn't defective ?

334
00:25:20,558 --> 00:25:22,160
Wha...?

335
00:25:23,360 --> 00:25:27,769
I mean, what if the runaways 
aren't caused by some bug...

336
00:25:27,769 --> 00:25:32,670
...but something 
intentionally programmed ?

337
00:25:41,278 --> 00:25:45,479
Would you read this for us ?
 This's the first report from Matsui.

338
00:25:49,068 --> 00:25:51,390
Report on Hoba Eiichi...

339
00:25:51,390 --> 00:25:52,390
Hoba ?...

340
00:25:52,390 --> 00:25:55,890
You mean Hoba Eiichi,
 the programmer ?

341
00:25:55,890 --> 00:26:00,590
Hoba Eiichi, the ace of Shinohara's 
software development division.

342
00:26:00,590 --> 00:26:03,700
He's the genius who 
single-handedly developed HOS.

343
00:26:03,700 --> 00:26:05,700
Or rather,
 he was...

344
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:07,298
Estimated age: 30.

345
00:26:07,298 --> 00:26:09,999
Returned from MlT in '97...

346
00:26:09,999 --> 00:26:11,999
...and was immediately hired 
by Shinohara Heavy lndustries.

347
00:26:11,999 --> 00:26:15,100
Address unknown. Profile unknown.
 Criminal record unknown.

348
00:26:15,100 --> 00:26:20,999
Approximately 170cm. Physical character,
 including major illnesses unknown...

349
00:26:20,999 --> 00:26:22,308
What lS this ?

350
00:26:22,308 --> 00:26:27,410
Not only Shinohara's personnel computer,
 but school, city hall...

351
00:26:27,410 --> 00:26:31,719
...and all of his personal 
records have been erased.

352
00:26:31,719 --> 00:26:33,318
He's far past the 
point of suspiscion...

353
00:26:33,318 --> 00:26:35,719
Then it's a piece of cake.

354
00:26:35,719 --> 00:26:37,719
Just bust him and bring 
him in for questioning.

355
00:26:37,719 --> 00:26:39,120
We can't.

356
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:40,318
Can't ?

357
00:26:40,318 --> 00:26:41,028
Why ?

358
00:26:41,028 --> 00:26:47,130
Five days ago he was sent to 
the Shinohara line at the Ark...

359
00:26:47,130 --> 00:26:49,729
...
and jumped into the sea.

360
00:26:49,729 --> 00:26:51,538
His body was never found.

361
00:26:57,840 --> 00:26:59,840
We certainly started 
a bit late on this.

362
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:02,840
Just when we started 
sniffing around HOS...

363
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:07,150
If we'd only done 
something earlier...Dammit.

364
00:27:07,150 --> 00:27:08,650
Oh, well.

365
00:27:08,650 --> 00:27:14,150
Bug...program...Either way it 
looks like HOS is the culprit.

366
00:27:14,150 --> 00:27:17,959
Now we have to figure out the big picture,
 and how Hoba fits in.

367
00:27:17,959 --> 00:27:21,860
We'll leave the investigation 
of Hoba to Matsui, and...

368
00:27:21,860 --> 00:27:24,360
Shinohara,
 why are you making a face ?

369
00:27:24,360 --> 00:27:28,450
Then you knew it 
was HOS all along.

370
00:27:28,450 --> 00:27:32,568
Boy, do l look like a fool,
 working all night...

371
00:27:32,568 --> 00:27:34,058
If nothing turns up,
 you WlLL.

372
00:27:34,058 --> 00:27:36,058
We still don't know what 
triggers the runaway.

373
00:27:36,058 --> 00:27:38,670
I want you to continue with your analysis,
 assuming of course you still want to ?

374
00:27:38,670 --> 00:27:39,870
YES !!!

375
00:27:39,870 --> 00:27:44,880
Oh, and this matter should just be 
between those of us in this room.

376
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:47,940
Why's that ?

377
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:50,180
Don't you remember ?

378
00:27:50,180 --> 00:27:55,989
Following last month's orders from above,
 Shige installed HOS in the Type 98's.

379
00:27:55,989 --> 00:28:00,390
If there's a relation between 
HOS and the runaways...

380
00:28:00,390 --> 00:28:02,590
...then the 98's 
are also at risk.

381
00:28:02,590 --> 00:28:05,090
Despite that, if there's a 
dispatch order, we have to go.

382
00:28:05,090 --> 00:28:08,900
Revealing this information would 
only serve to worry the men.

383
00:28:08,900 --> 00:28:10,999
I'm going over to Hachioji.

384
00:28:10,999 --> 00:28:12,298
Pops...

385
00:28:12,298 --> 00:28:15,190
I've got things l wanna check.

386
00:28:15,190 --> 00:28:17,798
I'm not gonna interfere 
with your investigation.

387
00:28:17,798 --> 00:28:19,308
I'd like to go too,
 Chief !

388
00:28:19,308 --> 00:28:20,999
Please, can l ?

389
00:28:20,999 --> 00:28:22,610
I probably don't have 
to tell you this, but...

390
00:28:22,610 --> 00:28:24,499
I'll behave myself !!!

391
00:28:35,318 --> 00:28:37,420
Wha'cha doing ?
 Move it !

392
00:28:37,420 --> 00:28:39,209
All right !

393
00:28:42,719 --> 00:28:43,420
Are you sure about this ?

394
00:28:43,420 --> 00:28:47,930
They'll be back by tonight. If we get a 
dispatch order l'll take over the command car.

395
00:28:47,930 --> 00:28:49,528
I don't get it.

396
00:28:49,528 --> 00:28:55,528
He's trying to prove that Shinohara 
lndustries is involved in this case.

397
00:28:55,528 --> 00:28:57,038
It's so ironic.

398
00:28:57,038 --> 00:28:59,840
The father's the president of 
a major Labor manufacturer...

399
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:02,239
...and the son's in 
the police Labor unit.

400
00:29:02,239 --> 00:29:05,538
On top of that they're constantly fighting,
 like cats and dogs.

401
00:29:05,538 --> 00:29:08,749
But it's up to Shinohara 
to make the decision.

402
00:29:08,749 --> 00:29:12,450
I don't like forcing people to make decisions,
 or ordering them to do so...

403
00:29:26,259 --> 00:29:29,959
Now that production for project 
Babylon is done for awhile...

404
00:29:29,959 --> 00:29:32,160
...we're concentrating 
on export.

405
00:29:32,160 --> 00:29:36,568
We just recently increased 
production on this line by 20%.

406
00:29:36,568 --> 00:29:39,269
I see.

407
00:29:39,269 --> 00:29:43,870
You know, even though l see this view every day,
 l still feel like l'm dreaming.

408
00:29:43,870 --> 00:29:47,778
Fifty years ago, we started a small parts 
factory for the US occupational force.

409
00:29:47,778 --> 00:29:50,278
Then we grew from vehicle 
parts to machine manufacturing.

410
00:29:50,278 --> 00:29:56,479
We started on industrial robot 
development the year Asuma was born.

411
00:29:56,479 --> 00:29:59,890
And now the monsters called 
Labors are flowing down the line.

412
00:29:59,890 --> 00:30:03,190
But l'm lost...

413
00:30:03,190 --> 00:30:08,690
I studied a lot, but fifth generation 
computer or system engineering...

414
00:30:08,690 --> 00:30:13,999
I just can't handle them. As a mechanic.
.. I really feel lonely...

415
00:30:13,999 --> 00:30:17,100
I'm just about the same.

416
00:30:17,100 --> 00:30:20,600
Everybody was constantly kicking me 
upstairs as a ``Vehicle God'' or something,

417
00:30:20,600 --> 00:30:23,610
but when it comes to software 
l'm basically a beginner...

418
00:30:23,610 --> 00:30:26,499
There's no way l can compete with 
Shige or any of the younger guys...

419
00:30:26,499 --> 00:30:29,110
But Sakaki...

420
00:30:29,110 --> 00:30:33,209
There's no point in fossil engineers 
sitting around comforting each other.

421
00:30:33,209 --> 00:30:36,719
No matter how technology develops,
 there's one thing that holds true.

422
00:30:36,719 --> 00:30:39,620
As long as the human side,
 those who make the machines...

423
00:30:39,620 --> 00:30:43,209
...those who maintain the machines,
 and those who handle the machines...

424
00:30:43,209 --> 00:30:48,830
...don't do anything bad,
 the machines won't play foul.

425
00:30:48,830 --> 00:30:55,028
But Jitsuyama, l didn't come here as 
the SV2 maintenance squad leader...

426
00:30:55,028 --> 00:30:59,229
...meeting the manager of Shinohara 
lndustries' Hachiouji factory.

427
00:30:59,229 --> 00:31:03,239
I came to speak openly, as men who spend 
more time with machines than with their wives.

428
00:31:03,239 --> 00:31:07,340
Your company's HOS,
 is it safe ?

429
00:31:08,239 --> 00:31:10,140
That sure wasn't what l 
expected you to say...

430
00:31:10,140 --> 00:31:13,850
This company's 
future depends on HOS.

431
00:31:13,850 --> 00:31:15,850
It's been well 
received everywhere.

432
00:31:15,850 --> 00:31:21,048
As a matter of fact, Project Babylon's 
construction time has been reduced by 30%.

433
00:31:21,048 --> 00:31:23,749
That's not what l'm asking.

434
00:31:26,058 --> 00:31:27,860
How is it ?

435
00:31:27,860 --> 00:31:29,360
It's safe.

436
00:31:29,360 --> 00:31:31,959
You have my guarantee.

437
00:31:40,870 --> 00:31:44,269
Okay,
 got the copy is finished.

438
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:53,278
The master copy of HOS...

439
00:32:18,798 --> 00:32:22,298
E...H...O..
.B...A......

440
00:32:22,298 --> 00:32:25,239
E.Hoba ?

441
00:33:09,538 --> 00:33:10,840
It's spreading rapidly !

442
00:33:10,840 --> 00:33:12,840
No, l don't know 
the exact rate !

443
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:14,440
What ?
 We can't do that !

444
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:18,150
Just do it !
 Shut down the main computer !

445
00:33:18,150 --> 00:33:22,450
Did you forget we're connected to the 
computers at other factories, too ? !

446
00:33:22,450 --> 00:33:23,850
That little twit !

447
00:33:30,058 --> 00:33:32,360
Damn !
 Did that surprise me or what ?

448
00:33:32,360 --> 00:33:35,058
Did you leave anything behind 
that they could trace back to you ?

449
00:33:35,058 --> 00:33:36,360
No way.

450
00:33:36,360 --> 00:33:40,058
But the only people who know the room's 
lock's combination me and Jitsuyama...

451
00:33:40,058 --> 00:33:41,670
...so they'll figure 
it out sooner or later.

452
00:33:41,670 --> 00:33:44,170
Guess we can't go back 
there for a while...

453
00:33:44,170 --> 00:33:45,870
But we did get the 
data we needed.

454
00:33:45,870 --> 00:33:49,170
If something that risky 
is in the master copy...

455
00:33:49,170 --> 00:33:52,778
...then even Shinohara lndustries 
hasn't broken the protection on HOS.

456
00:33:52,778 --> 00:33:57,479
We have eight thousand Labors lurking 
around Tokyo with a suspicious OS...

457
00:33:57,479 --> 00:33:59,778
...and God only 
knows what's in it.

458
00:33:59,778 --> 00:34:01,180
It's bad news alright...

459
00:34:01,180 --> 00:34:05,489
...and sooner or later some of the 
sharper folks'll start to notice.

460
00:34:05,489 --> 00:34:08,488
Eventually Noa 
will find out too.

461
00:34:08,488 --> 00:34:10,989
We'd better deal 
with this quickly.

462
00:34:10,989 --> 00:34:12,289
Yes, sir !

463
00:36:50,318 --> 00:36:52,318
We can see that again...

464
00:36:52,318 --> 00:36:54,119
Oh ?

465
00:36:54,119 --> 00:36:57,128
We saw it from every room...

466
00:36:57,128 --> 00:37:00,230
...but that's pretty 
common in today's Tokyo...

467
00:37:00,230 --> 00:37:02,028
...
must be a coincidence.

468
00:37:03,230 --> 00:37:06,429
I still don't get this Hoba guy.

469
00:37:06,429 --> 00:37:10,338
I mean Labor related jobs have 
really high salaries, right ?

470
00:37:10,338 --> 00:37:15,438
So why did he choose all these battered 
apartments; 26 of them in three years ?

471
00:37:15,438 --> 00:37:20,139
Don't you think it might be the 
best way to keep from being traced,

472
00:37:20,139 --> 00:37:25,349
Buildings about to be demolished to make way for 
redevelopment are just as good as battered ones.

473
00:37:25,349 --> 00:37:27,750
No neighbors to be interrogated.

474
00:37:27,750 --> 00:37:32,750
If he was that cautious, then why'd he leave 
behind a change-of-address at city hall ?

475
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:37,159
And this after breaking 
into the files...

476
00:37:37,159 --> 00:37:40,759
...and not only erasing his 
personal data at work...

477
00:37:40,759 --> 00:37:43,159
...
but at his school over-seas.

478
00:37:43,159 --> 00:37:45,659
As if he were showing off,
 eh ?

479
00:37:47,869 --> 00:37:48,468
Hey, Officers.

480
00:37:48,468 --> 00:37:50,968
You through yet ?

