727
00:51:44,648 --> 00:51:47,750
I could ask you the same thing.
 What're you doing in street clothes ?

728
00:51:47,750 --> 00:51:51,449
Well, this and that happened and 
l got suspended for two weeks.

729
00:51:51,449 --> 00:51:54,849
If you'd talked to us beforehand 
that may not have happened.

730
00:51:54,849 --> 00:51:58,059
It's the price you pay for 
not thinking about teamwork.

731
00:51:58,059 --> 00:52:01,659
Oh ? Which button do l have to 
push to make you say ``teamwork'' ?

732
00:52:01,858 --> 00:52:03,059
WHAT ?!

733
00:52:03,059 --> 00:52:04,858
Please, calm down,
 both of you...

734
00:52:04,858 --> 00:52:09,769
...try to honor 
my safe return...

735
00:52:09,769 --> 00:52:13,568
Oh, Shige, please fill out the 
form for program re-writing.

736
00:52:13,568 --> 00:52:16,568
Right ! Sorry to put you to work as 
soon you get back, but could you ?

737
00:52:16,568 --> 00:52:17,568
Do a rewrite ?

738
00:52:17,568 --> 00:52:18,468
Yeah !

739
00:52:18,468 --> 00:52:19,168
For the 98 ?

740
00:52:19,168 --> 00:52:21,059
Of the OS !

741
00:52:22,579 --> 00:52:26,378
What's the problem ?!
 We can't have HOS aboard !

742
00:52:26,378 --> 00:52:30,278
It's the reason l was killing myself working.
..and got suspended...

743
00:52:30,278 --> 00:52:32,480
I never did the rewrite to HOS.

744
00:52:32,480 --> 00:52:34,889
What ?! But we got the 
order from headquarters...

745
00:52:34,889 --> 00:52:38,789
So, l just pretended to rewrite.
 I threw in a dummy activation display...

746
00:52:38,789 --> 00:52:41,389
...
and sent back the diskette.

747
00:52:41,389 --> 00:52:46,699
Inside is the same old OS.
 You didn't have any problems, did you ?

748
00:52:46,699 --> 00:52:50,798
Well, l sure was glad when l got the news 
over there that HOS was a chancy thing.

749
00:52:50,798 --> 00:52:53,489
But it's all thanks 
to Sakaki's training.

750
00:52:53,489 --> 00:52:58,099
Even if it was good, l didn't feel 
like putting in some suspicious new HOS.

751
00:52:58,099 --> 00:53:00,809
If anything happened l'd 
take full responsibility.

752
00:53:00,809 --> 00:53:05,699
So off l went, secret in my heart.
 Well, it sure was a success !

753
00:53:05,699 --> 00:53:07,409
Right ?

754
00:53:07,409 --> 00:53:09,909
But nobody ever heard about it ?

755
00:53:09,909 --> 00:53:15,418
Funny...I told Goto when he called 
me international long-distance...

756
00:53:15,418 --> 00:53:17,019
You told the Chief ?

757
00:53:17,019 --> 00:53:18,619
In other words,
 he knew that if he didn't tell you..

758
00:53:18,619 --> 00:53:22,918
...you'd work hard 
enough to kill yourself.

759
00:53:22,918 --> 00:53:25,929
He's at it again...

760
00:53:25,929 --> 00:53:28,329
Now l know how Noa 
was feeling earlier...

761
00:53:28,329 --> 00:53:33,128
He's been playing me like a puppet.
..That middle-aged weasel...

762
00:53:33,128 --> 00:53:34,929
Poor Asuma...

763
00:53:34,929 --> 00:53:37,739
A CURSE ON HlM !

764
00:54:46,289 --> 00:54:48,389
1-3 Eiichi Hoba...

765
00:54:59,188 --> 00:55:00,099
Hey !

766
00:55:00,298 --> 00:55:02,000
It's in English...

767
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:11,909
``He bound the heavens also, and came down,
 and darkness was under his feet''

768
00:55:11,909 --> 00:55:15,619
...It's one of the psalms 
in the Old Testament.

769
00:55:15,619 --> 00:55:19,210
It must've been written 
there by Hoba himself.

770
00:55:19,210 --> 00:55:23,210
But l still can't believe you 
found the house where he was born.

771
00:55:23,210 --> 00:55:27,329
It was nothing. All l did was trace address 
changes and that's where l ended up.

772
00:55:27,329 --> 00:55:32,429
But that's it,
 l can't go any further...dead end.

773
00:55:32,429 --> 00:55:35,829
That area of town was 
deserted during the 80s...

774
00:55:35,829 --> 00:55:38,730
...when there was that sharp 
increase in land prices.

775
00:55:38,730 --> 00:55:42,039
After the National Land 
Act it was forgotten.

776
00:55:42,039 --> 00:55:47,438
But how strange this city is...

777
00:55:48,139 --> 00:55:56,548
As l traced his path l started to feel 
as though time were leaving me behind...

778
00:55:56,548 --> 00:56:03,659
What you think of as a familiar sight 
starts to rot away here and there...

779
00:56:03,659 --> 00:56:06,759
...you look away for a moment 
and when you turn back it's gone.

780
00:56:06,759 --> 00:56:11,159
Gone before you even 
know what it meant.

781
00:56:11,159 --> 00:56:15,938
In this town,
 the past is a worthless thing...

782
00:56:16,239 --> 00:56:18,468
Look at it this way.

783
00:56:18,468 --> 00:56:20,869
The place where we're talking now 
was sea until a little while ago.

784
00:56:20,869 --> 00:56:25,568
And in a few years there'll 
be a huge city in front of us.

785
00:56:25,568 --> 00:56:30,778
And then, someday,
 that will become the worthless past.

786
00:56:30,778 --> 00:56:34,480
It's like a continual bad joke.

787
00:56:34,480 --> 00:56:39,480
That's probably what 
Hoba was trying to say...

788
00:56:42,088 --> 00:56:45,938
``Where do we go..
.? What are we ?''

789
00:56:46,139 --> 00:56:47,389
What's that ?

790
00:56:47,389 --> 00:56:48,889
An inscription.

791
00:56:48,889 --> 00:56:55,099
It was left on a wall by a 
Viking captain in ancient Europe.

792
00:56:56,798 --> 00:57:00,188
You bozo !
 Snap it harder !

793
00:57:00,188 --> 00:57:02,298
Well...
Sorry about all this...

794
00:57:02,298 --> 00:57:04,699
Before you go...

795
00:57:11,409 --> 00:57:15,608
What's your opinion ?

796
00:57:15,608 --> 00:57:19,718
He's it, Goto,
 no mistake.

797
00:57:19,718 --> 00:57:25,619
But if he's a goner, then l guess there's 
not much more an inspector can do...

798
00:57:25,619 --> 00:57:30,028
Well, l owe you for this one.
 I'll make it up to you some day...

799
00:57:30,028 --> 00:57:35,929
A tomato patch, a chicken house,
 and the maintenance crews are all out fishing...

800
00:57:35,929 --> 00:57:39,628
...do they really call 
themselves police ?

801
00:57:39,628 --> 00:57:42,438
Not police...

802
00:57:42,438 --> 00:57:45,438
More like defenders of justice.

803
00:57:46,699 --> 00:57:48,563
Tell me, do you think I'm 
still over-analyzing ?

804
00:57:49,000 --> 00:57:50,398
What ?

805
00:57:50,398 --> 00:57:52,398
I can't say really...

806
00:57:52,398 --> 00:57:57,398
...but I am grateful that the defect was 
found before we actually got the Type 0.

807
00:57:57,398 --> 00:58:01,798
I asked Kanuka to do research 
on Hoba's stay at MIT.

808
00:58:01,798 --> 00:58:04,699
While he was there 
he was called Jehovah.

809
00:58:04,699 --> 00:58:05,898
Jehovah ?

810
00:58:05,898 --> 00:58:08,710
That's what they call 
God in the Old Testament.

811
00:58:08,710 --> 00:58:12,309
It sounds alot like his real name,
 and he was probably smart enough to earn it.

812
00:58:12,309 --> 00:58:15,108
Well, actually there's a 
follow-up story to that.

813
00:58:15,108 --> 00:58:19,809
The proper pronunciation is 
``Yah-weh'' or ``Yah-ha-weh''.

814
00:58:19,809 --> 00:58:24,608
``Je-ho-va'' is an incorrect 
one that spread by accident.

815
00:58:24,608 --> 00:58:28,710
When he found that out 
he was insanely happy.

816
00:58:28,710 --> 00:58:33,318
You know, Shinobu, I'm starting to feel I 
understand the way this Hoba guy thinks.

817
00:58:33,318 --> 00:58:35,718
Looking at those high-rises...

818
00:58:35,718 --> 00:58:40,218
...day after day,
 wondering what kind of crime to commit.

819
00:58:43,218 --> 00:58:50,218
``And the Lord came down to 
see the city and the tower...

820
00:58:50,218 --> 00:58:52,028
...which the children of men builded.
  (Genesis 11-5)

821
00:58:52,028 --> 00:58:54,429
Therefore is the name 
of it called Babel;

822
00:58:54,429 --> 00:58:59,730
...because there did the Lord 
confound the language of the earth;

823
00:58:59,730 --> 00:59:03,128
...and from thence did the Lord scatter 
them abroad upon the face of the earth.

824
00:59:06,329 --> 00:59:08,218
Well,
 it could be coincidence...

825
00:59:08,218 --> 00:59:11,829
Do you think it's a coincidence that he 
chose the Ark as the place to kill himself ?

826
00:59:11,829 --> 00:59:15,639
If this plan centers on a 
code based on the Bible...

827
00:59:15,639 --> 00:59:19,039
...there's no way he's going to pass 
over a target like Project Babylon.

828
00:59:19,039 --> 00:59:21,539
There's more to come.

829
00:59:21,539 --> 00:59:24,838
These are clues 
left by Hoba himself.

830
00:59:24,838 --> 00:59:31,438
Another example.
 He made it a point to leave messages.

831
00:59:31,438 --> 00:59:35,039
All 23 of the places 
Hoba lived in...

832
00:59:35,039 --> 00:59:38,148
...overlap with the three Labor 
runaway zones that Asuma pointed out.

833
00:59:38,148 --> 00:59:40,349
Matsui was really puzzled.

834
00:59:40,349 --> 00:59:43,349
He said it was as though Hoba was 
asking us to solve the mystery.

835
00:59:43,349 --> 00:59:44,349
A challenge ?

836
00:59:44,349 --> 00:59:47,048
He's not that sort of romantic.

837
00:59:47,048 --> 00:59:50,048
He wasn't going up 
against the police at all.

838
00:59:50,048 --> 00:59:53,750
He had great confidence 
in his program...

839
00:59:53,750 --> 00:59:58,048
...or else he wouldn't have 
died before seeing the result.

840
00:59:58,048 --> 00:59:59,648
When he jumped off he was 
probably laughing at us...

841
00:59:59,648 --> 01:00:05,960
No, everybody who 
lives in this city...

842
01:00:07,349 --> 01:00:13,460
You know, you look so happy 
when you talk about Hoba.

843
01:00:13,460 --> 01:00:14,559
Eh...?

844
01:00:14,559 --> 01:00:16,059
...
that's dangerous...

845
01:00:16,059 --> 01:00:17,460
Really ?

846
01:00:19,759 --> 01:00:23,968
Anyway, if it's that big a plot,
 are you sure those two can handle it ?

847
01:00:23,968 --> 01:00:25,099
I think they'll be okay...

848
01:00:34,968 --> 01:00:38,068
I'm sleepy...hungry .
..and worn out.

849
01:00:38,068 --> 01:00:40,858
Okay,
 input's complete...

850
01:00:44,369 --> 01:00:46,179
Here we go...

851
01:00:51,179 --> 01:00:53,679
Okay...what's the parameter 
for the simulation program ?

852
01:00:53,679 --> 01:00:57,778
Well, if 10.21Hz is the right number,
 then this is correct...

853
01:00:57,778 --> 01:01:01,079
That's all the 
damage there'd be ?

854
01:01:01,079 --> 01:01:03,489
...I feel like 
I'm dealing blind.

855
01:01:07,188 --> 01:01:09,588
I don't get it...

856
01:01:13,789 --> 01:01:16,889
I know it couldn't end 
with this little...

857
01:01:16,889 --> 01:01:19,088
What data could be missing ?

858
01:01:19,088 --> 01:01:23,188
That inaccessible file in HOS...

859
01:01:23,188 --> 01:01:28,088
If that could be taken apart we could 
prove Goto's theory about Hoba's crime.

860
01:01:28,088 --> 01:01:31,699
Then we could spend more 
resources and personnel...

861
01:01:31,699 --> 01:01:33,099
Then it's a Trojan 
Horse program ?

862
01:01:33,099 --> 01:01:35,000
Probably...

863
01:01:35,000 --> 01:01:38,398
That rewrite must've worsened the contamination,
 spread it even further...

864
01:01:38,398 --> 01:01:40,500
Such a stupid decision...

865
01:01:40,500 --> 01:01:43,699
Shige !
 You have a guest !

866
01:01:45,398 --> 01:01:46,699
I've brought provisions !

867
01:01:46,699 --> 01:01:48,599
How's it going ?

868
01:01:48,599 --> 01:01:51,309
It just proved how 
powerless we are...

869
01:01:51,309 --> 01:01:53,210
That's it ?

870
01:01:53,210 --> 01:01:54,309
Here,
 I got a newspaper

871
01:01:54,309 --> 01:01:55,909
Thanks.

872
01:01:55,909 --> 01:01:58,210
Let's see how our international 
affairs are doing...

873
01:01:58,210 --> 01:02:03,710
Compared to ``God'' I feel like 
a computer-loving little kid...

874
01:02:03,710 --> 01:02:06,108
Noa, coulld you get 
me some coffee ?

875
01:02:06,108 --> 01:02:08,210
Oooooo, sounds good.
 I only have instant; sorry.

876
01:02:08,210 --> 01:02:09,608
Sure thing.

877
01:02:20,608 --> 01:02:21,918
Noa,
 turn on the gas again !

878
01:02:21,918 --> 01:02:22,918
Huh ?!

879
01:02:22,918 --> 01:02:23,918
Just do it !

880
01:02:23,918 --> 01:02:25,818
What's this all about ?

881
01:02:29,418 --> 01:02:31,019
So what ?....

882
01:02:41,028 --> 01:02:41,829
What the... ?

883
01:02:41,829 --> 01:02:43,218
The resonance !

884
01:02:44,128 --> 01:02:48,028
There was no point in simulating 
the components individually...

885
01:02:48,028 --> 01:02:50,218
...if objects vibrate at 
the same fixed frequency...

886
01:02:50,218 --> 01:02:54,218
...frequency they reinforce 
each other's vibrations !

887
01:02:59,230 --> 01:03:00,938
Not much of a difference.

888
01:03:00,938 --> 01:03:04,838
The low frequency that initiates 
the first resonance is too weak.

889
01:03:04,838 --> 01:03:07,938
It has to kick off with 
something more powerful !

890
01:03:07,938 --> 01:03:10,639
Blow-through structure buildings,
 the harp bridge...

891
01:03:10,639 --> 01:03:12,539
...iron pipes in construction sites,
 air ducts for underground facilities...

892
01:03:12,539 --> 01:03:14,539
There's gotta be 
something else...

893
01:03:14,539 --> 01:03:20,048
Let's see...it should be located in some 
big open space...with no outer walls...

894
01:03:20,048 --> 01:03:22,449
...say some multi-level 
structure...

895
01:03:22,449 --> 01:03:24,849
How could something like that 
exist in crowded Tokyo...!!

896
01:03:39,048 --> 01:03:40,849
The Ark ?!

897
01:03:40,849 --> 01:03:42,858
How could we have 
been so blind ?!

898
01:03:42,858 --> 01:03:45,759
I forgot that I made a copy 
at the Hachiouji factory...

899
01:03:45,759 --> 01:03:48,559
Put the Ark into the 
wind tunnel simulation...

900
01:03:48,559 --> 01:03:52,159
...raise the windspeed parameter to infinity,
 and throw the lot into our first simulation...

901
01:03:52,159 --> 01:03:55,059
Hang on ! This computer doesn't 
have the processing capacity.

902
01:03:57,960 --> 01:03:59,759
Okay,
 we've got the Fridge online !

903
01:04:08,369 --> 01:04:10,068
The data's not coming back,
 is it ?

904
01:04:10,068 --> 01:04:11,769
Here it is !

905
01:04:18,269 --> 01:04:19,659
Wow....

906
01:04:21,369 --> 01:04:23,068
What's the lowest wind velocity 
that can set off the reaction ?

907
01:04:24,659 --> 01:04:26,468
...
40 m/second ?!!

908
01:04:26,468 --> 01:04:30,179
Damn...You only get that sort 
of wind when a Typhoon hits...

909
01:04:38,679 --> 01:04:39,579
 ...and so this rather 
powerful Typhoon, #19,

910
01:04:39,579 --> 01:04:41,480
 ...is now at the south 
west tip of Kei Peninsula...

911
01:04:41,480 --> 01:04:44,179
 ...heading north east 
at a speed of 25 kmph.

912
01:04:44,179 --> 01:04:47,878
 It will hit Tokyo 
early tomorrow morning.

913
01:04:47,878 --> 01:04:49,688
 The typhoon's air 
pressure is 950 bar...

914
01:04:49,688 --> 01:04:55,699
 ...and within 25 km of its center 
wind speeds are over 40 m/second...

915
01:04:56,188 --> 01:04:58,588
That's it !
 We've heard enough !

916
01:04:58,588 --> 01:05:01,588
This is all just a theory !

917
01:05:01,588 --> 01:05:05,099
And I heard that this 
simulation was programmed by...

918
01:05:05,099 --> 01:05:08,188
...a suspended officer 
and the maintenance crew.

919
01:05:08,188 --> 01:05:12,599
Do you really expect us 
to take it seriously ?

920
01:05:12,599 --> 01:05:14,699
According to the 
Meteorological Agency...

921
01:05:14,699 --> 01:05:18,699
...Typhoon #19 will strike the 
city early the next morning.

922
01:05:18,699 --> 01:05:21,398
We don't have time for 
additional testing of the program.

923
01:05:21,398 --> 01:05:24,099
You say it's only 
an unproven theory...

924
01:05:24,099 --> 01:05:29,199
...but it's a fact that we have 
no evidence to deny it either.

925
01:05:29,798 --> 01:05:33,398
When the Typhoon reaches Tokyo its heavy 
winds will cause the Ark to vibrate...

926
01:05:33,398 --> 01:05:37,409
That will stimulate the low-frequency howling 
of the numerous high-rises at the water front,

927
01:05:37,409 --> 01:05:39,409
...which will itself induce the whirring 
of the buildings in downtown Tokyo.

928
01:05:39,409 --> 01:05:42,608
And 8000 Labors situated all over the 
metropolis will become runaways....

929
01:05:42,608 --> 01:05:46,710
What will result 
need not be mentioned.

930
01:05:46,710 --> 01:05:51,009
Labors aren't just located in the 
redevelopments around the bay, but also...

931
01:05:51,009 --> 01:05:54,909
...in the city center, and in the Geo-front 
construction site 100 meters underground.

932
01:05:54,909 --> 01:05:58,218
Also Labors are operating 
inside some nuclear reactors.

933
01:05:58,218 --> 01:06:01,318
If the simulation 
results become reality...

934
01:06:01,318 --> 01:06:04,818
...I'd like to know who 
would take responsibility...

935
01:06:04,818 --> 01:06:09,019
...and how, for not preventing 
the crime beforehand.

936
01:06:10,519 --> 01:06:11,608
Goto.

937
01:06:11,608 --> 01:06:15,818
The city-wide OS rewite 
has been completed.

938
01:06:15,818 --> 01:06:23,528
Even if Eiichi Hoba's crime existed,
 it is now quite irrelevent, don't you think ?

939
01:06:23,528 --> 01:06:27,429
HOS is still being analyzed,
 with the assisstance of MIT...

940
01:06:27,429 --> 01:06:32,028
...but it's true nature has 
not yet been determined.

941
01:06:32,028 --> 01:06:35,028
The experts agree that it may still 
be hiding in the Labors' memories...

942
01:06:35,028 --> 01:06:38,528
...in that case it is reasonable 
to assume that any Labors...

943
01:06:38,528 --> 01:06:41,639
...that came in contact with 
HOS are still contaminated.

944
01:06:41,639 --> 01:06:43,639
Wait for the Typhoon to hit ?

945
01:06:43,639 --> 01:06:48,039
Chop down the high-rises ?
 Dismantle all 8000 Labors ?

946
01:06:48,039 --> 01:06:49,539
Or...

947
01:06:50,230 --> 01:06:51,539
You have only four choices.

948
01:06:51,539 --> 01:06:54,639
Your decision please.

949
01:06:55,739 --> 01:06:59,438
From early tomorrow until 
the typhoon has passed...

950
01:06:59,438 --> 01:07:02,438
...activation of all Labors within 
city limits will be prohibited.

951
01:07:02,438 --> 01:07:06,349
Labor production lines and repair 
facilities will be shut down.

952
01:07:06,349 --> 01:07:10,750
We will request aid from the fire 
department and the defence ministry...

953
01:07:10,750 --> 01:07:12,949
...as well as 
neighboring prefectures.

954
01:07:12,949 --> 01:07:13,949
That is all.

955
01:07:15,548 --> 01:07:19,750
Chief, there's a possibility that deactivated 
Labors may start up by themselves...

956
01:07:19,750 --> 01:07:21,750
...due to the effects of 
the low frequency noise.

957
01:07:21,750 --> 01:07:25,159
Did you forget about the episode 
with the JSDF prototype Labor...

958
01:07:25,159 --> 01:07:26,159
Goto !

959
01:07:26,159 --> 01:07:27,259
What was that ?

960
01:07:27,259 --> 01:07:31,648
 I never received such a report.

961
01:07:29,648 --> 01:07:31,648
 Then I have one more question.

962
01:07:31,648 --> 01:07:34,349
Will you knock it off ?!

963
01:07:34,349 --> 01:07:41,159
If it's caused by a Typhoon, I don't really 
see how anyone should be held responsible...

964
01:07:41,159 --> 01:07:43,349
I mean it's done by a Typhoon...

965
01:07:46,559 --> 01:07:49,369
Of course. If it's an act of God,
 it can't be helped...

966
01:07:49,369 --> 01:07:50,659
Chief !!!

967
01:07:52,369 --> 01:07:55,159
Assistant Inspector Goto,
 returning to the station.

968
01:07:56,659 --> 01:07:57,659
What did he mean ?

969
01:07:57,659 --> 01:08:01,159
As he said, it can't be 
helped if it's an act of God.

970
01:08:01,159 --> 01:08:04,659
Afterwards, if Hoba's 
crime can be proven, fine.

971
01:08:04,659 --> 01:08:08,159
If not, let it go as 
the Typhoon's fault.

972
01:08:08,159 --> 01:08:12,579
If the cat gets let out of the bag,
 the Captain'll take the fall.

973
01:08:12,579 --> 01:08:14,369
The old snake.

974
01:08:14,369 --> 01:08:15,679
Poor Captain...

975
01:08:15,679 --> 01:08:17,778
We're the poor ones.

976
01:08:17,778 --> 01:08:20,979
If Hoba's crime can't be proved,
 we'll be criminals.

977
01:08:20,979 --> 01:08:22,778
Want out ?

978
01:08:22,778 --> 01:08:26,880
No. If I'm gonna regret it anyway,
 better something done than left undone.

979
01:08:26,880 --> 01:08:28,880
Well then.

980
01:08:32,988 --> 01:08:34,688
No turning back now.

981
01:08:34,688 --> 01:08:36,789
I won't be back for awhile.
 Follow Shinobu's orders until then will you ?

982
01:08:36,789 --> 01:08:38,789
Roger !

983
01:08:39,988 --> 01:08:42,688
What's gonna happen ?

984
01:08:42,688 --> 01:08:44,789
We're gonna destroy the Ark !

985
01:08:50,188 --> 01:08:53,789
After insulating the memory bank and the cockpit,
 get on with the water-proofing.

986
01:08:53,789 --> 01:08:55,000
We don't have much time !

987
01:08:55,000 --> 01:08:57,199
Boss !
 The floats are here !

988
01:08:57,199 --> 01:09:01,199
Okay, let group 3 handle it ! As the crews 
finish their current jobs I'll send them down !

989
01:09:01,199 --> 01:09:04,699
I got the okay !
 Bring out the riot gun too !

990
01:09:04,699 --> 01:09:07,000
We got the experimental 
explosive shells, right ?!

991
01:09:07,000 --> 01:09:09,398
Load 'em into cartridges !

992
01:09:09,398 --> 01:09:11,699
What ?
 But that's too risky...

993
01:09:11,699 --> 01:09:13,099
DO IT !!!

994
01:09:13,099 --> 01:09:14,898
 Typhoon #19 is 
continuing on course.

995
01:09:14,898 --> 01:09:20,309
 It is still heading north east,
 and will hit the Kanto area in...

996
01:09:20,309 --> 01:09:23,010
YES ! THE STORM IS COMING !
 THE STORM IS COMING !

997
01:09:24,409 --> 01:09:29,809
We'll have to purge the platforms with 
the emergency fire systems after all...

998
01:09:29,809 --> 01:09:33,608
Then the occupation of the 
control center is the key...

999
01:09:33,608 --> 01:09:35,510
Give me the file on 
the security robots...

1000
01:09:55,608 --> 01:10:00,608
Labors are set up...Attaching the floats to 
the trailers'll be done in a couple hours...

1001
01:10:00,608 --> 01:10:03,829
By the way, how did you get hold 
of that monster anti-Labor rifle ?

1002
01:10:03,829 --> 01:10:06,929
I begged for one from the 
paratroop unit in Kasumigaura.

1003
01:10:06,929 --> 01:10:12,000
When I mentioned the prototype Labor 
incident they rented me one immediately.

1004
01:10:12,000 --> 01:10:14,000
I'm going over to 
Narita airport now.

1005
01:10:14,000 --> 01:10:17,220
We may have to fight every Labor on 
the Ark so I called in a secret weapon.

1006
01:10:17,220 --> 01:10:20,528
Yes,
 I mean HER.

1007
01:10:30,938 --> 01:10:32,639
``Sight seeing ?''

1008
01:10:32,639 --> 01:10:34,539
``No...''

1009
01:10:36,539 --> 01:10:37,938
``Combat.''

1010
01:10:54,648 --> 01:10:56,148
Let the air in !

1011
01:11:05,050 --> 01:11:07,750
There's nothing 
more for me to say.

1012
01:11:07,750 --> 01:11:11,648
The Ark should be totally empty 
after the evacuation order...

1013
01:11:11,648 --> 01:11:13,349
...so fight as 
much as you like !

1014
01:11:30,559 --> 01:11:34,769
ALRIGHT !
 GIVE IT ALL YOU'VE GOT !

1015
01:11:45,269 --> 01:11:48,769
Are you sure ?
 You can still call them back !

1016
01:11:48,769 --> 01:11:52,769
What if the operation is successful but 
you still can't prove Hoba's crime ?

1017
01:11:52,769 --> 01:11:55,278
Then we're criminals.

1018
01:11:55,278 --> 01:11:59,979
But if we don't do anything,
 and there's a disaster ?

1019
01:11:59,979 --> 01:12:01,579
Then we're criminals again.

1020
01:12:01,579 --> 01:12:02,679
Which do you prefer ?

1021
01:12:04,369 --> 01:12:09,179
And besides,
 there was no choice to begin with.

1022
01:12:09,179 --> 01:12:15,988
If they fail,
 the bay area will be devastated.

1023
01:12:15,988 --> 01:12:22,289
If they succeed, then project Babylon 
will be crippled by the loss of the Ark.

1024
01:12:22,289 --> 01:12:25,289
Either way we lose.

1025
01:12:25,289 --> 01:12:30,688
Probably the real fight 
ended when Hoba jumped.

1026
01:12:30,688 --> 01:12:32,188
Don't you agree ?

1027
01:12:32,188 --> 01:12:33,889
And you still want to do this ?

1028
01:12:33,889 --> 01:12:36,188
You really don't have the right 
character to be in the police...

1029
01:12:36,188 --> 01:12:39,398
I really feel sorry that you always end 
up getting the short end of the stick.

1030
01:12:39,398 --> 01:12:41,300
Where are you going ?

1031
01:12:41,300 --> 01:12:43,599
We did get silent approval 
from headquarters...

1032
01:12:43,599 --> 01:12:46,898
...but if they raise 
hell on the Ark...

1033
01:12:46,898 --> 01:12:51,199
...the Maritime Safety Agency and the 
Ports and Harbors Bureau won't keep quiet.

1034
01:12:51,199 --> 01:12:54,599
I'll go over there 
and buy some time.

1035
01:12:54,599 --> 01:12:57,300
This's a job for the chief.

1036
01:12:57,300 --> 01:12:58,099
Goto...

1037
01:12:58,099 --> 01:12:59,099
Yes ?

1038
01:12:59,099 --> 01:13:00,809
...No,
 nothing...

1039
01:13:00,809 --> 01:13:03,010
Then, please take care of 
the rescue arrangements.

1040
01:13:22,210 --> 01:13:24,220
There it is !
 500 meters ahead !

1041
01:13:24,220 --> 01:13:25,420
The Ark !

1042
01:14:06,099 --> 01:14:08,539
Doesn't the 
atmosphere feel Evil ?

1043
01:14:08,539 --> 01:14:11,438
Just like a shrine of Idols.

1044
01:14:11,438 --> 01:14:14,639
An appropriate grave for a man 
who assumed the name of the Lord.

1045
01:14:14,639 --> 01:14:18,639
Listen, as long as they don't get too close,
 guard robots aren't much of a concern.

1046
01:14:18,639 --> 01:14:24,139
But there's far too many of them,
 so avoid combat as much as possible !

1047
01:14:24,139 --> 01:14:27,938
Ohta, take the point !
 Noa, bring up the rear !

1048
01:14:27,938 --> 01:14:29,648
We'll run all the way !

1049
01:14:29,648 --> 01:14:31,648
CHAAAAAARGE !!!

1050
01:14:39,550 --> 01:14:41,449
Come on you worthless 
hunks of junk !

1051
01:14:41,449 --> 01:14:43,050
I'll rip you apart !

1052
01:15:09,349 --> 01:15:11,159
Five to the rear...

1053
01:15:11,159 --> 01:15:14,159
Eight...
They keep coming !

1054
01:15:18,470 --> 01:15:19,470
Wait up !

1055
01:15:19,470 --> 01:15:20,769
Move it !

1056
01:15:28,470 --> 01:15:30,568
I told you to avoid combat !

1057
01:15:30,568 --> 01:15:33,970
We did,
 as much as possible.

1058
01:15:33,970 --> 01:15:35,858
Quick response based 
on the situation !

1059
01:15:35,858 --> 01:15:39,479
The situation is 
changing all the time !

1060
01:15:39,479 --> 01:15:41,369
At any rate,
 conserve ammo !

1061
01:15:41,369 --> 01:15:43,369
We don't know what's up there !

1062
01:15:43,369 --> 01:15:44,778
Roger !

1063
01:16:04,988 --> 01:16:06,289
There it is !

1064
01:16:17,188 --> 01:16:18,488
Move it !

1065
01:16:18,488 --> 01:16:21,199
He's so rough,
 dammit...

1066
01:16:21,199 --> 01:16:24,300
If we don't hurry this place is gonna 
be flooded with security robots !

1067
01:16:24,500 --> 01:16:26,398
Start up the 
emergency routines !

1068
01:16:26,398 --> 01:16:28,699
That'll shut off the 
security automatically !

1069
01:16:32,300 --> 01:16:35,099
Okay,
 here we go...

1070
01:16:35,300 --> 01:16:37,800
This will've sounded 
the alarm back on land.

1071
01:16:37,800 --> 01:16:41,898
Well then let's see if we'll 
be dangerous criminals...

1072
01:16:41,898 --> 01:16:45,710
...or heroes by the time the 
Maritime Safety people get here.

1073
01:16:45,710 --> 01:16:47,210
We have until the 
weather clears.

1074
01:16:50,510 --> 01:16:53,409
Can you hear me ?
 I've deactivated the security systems.

1075
01:16:53,409 --> 01:16:54,608
 Roger !

1076
01:16:54,608 --> 01:16:56,210
 Will stand guard !

1077
01:16:58,510 --> 01:17:00,309
Okay,
 let's take this thing apart !

1078
01:17:01,309 --> 01:17:02,108
W...wait !

1079
01:17:02,108 --> 01:17:02,608
What ?

1080
01:17:02,608 --> 01:17:04,108
A person !

1081
01:17:04,108 --> 01:17:06,608
There's somebody in 
subcontrol on the top level !

1082
01:17:06,608 --> 01:17:07,519
WHAT ?!

1083
01:17:10,220 --> 01:17:11,608
It's no mistake.

1084
01:17:11,608 --> 01:17:13,119
See ?
 It's moving...

1085
01:17:20,608 --> 01:17:23,519
It can't be...

1086
01:17:23,519 --> 01:17:26,119
But he's supposed to be dead,
 isn't he ?

1087
01:17:26,119 --> 01:17:27,729
Hoba's ghost ?!

1088
01:17:27,729 --> 01:17:31,220
Or some sort of trap. Can you get me 
into communication with the subcontrol ?

1089
01:17:31,220 --> 01:17:35,130
Can't.
 The subcontrol isn't in use...

1090
01:17:35,130 --> 01:17:36,929
It has to be powered 
up from there.

1091
01:17:36,929 --> 01:17:38,829
Someone has to 
go up and check...

1092
01:17:38,829 --> 01:17:40,429
But the time !

1093
01:17:40,429 --> 01:17:43,028
The Typhoon's about to hit !

1094
01:17:50,028 --> 01:17:51,840
 Noa !
 Listen up !

1095
01:17:51,840 --> 01:17:52,938
What is it ?

1096
01:17:52,938 --> 01:17:54,229
 We've got a problem.

1097
01:17:54,229 --> 01:17:57,229
 There's a possibility that someone's still here,
 in the top floor subcontrol.

1098
01:17:57,229 --> 01:18:01,340
 A file cross-check 
says it's Eiichi Hoba.

1099
01:18:01,340 --> 01:18:03,438
 It's a trap for sure !

1100
01:18:03,438 --> 01:18:05,738
 But somebody's still up there.

1101
01:18:05,738 --> 01:18:07,438
 Noa,
 will you go ?

1102
01:18:07,639 --> 01:18:09,139
Why Me ?!

1103
01:18:09,139 --> 01:18:10,539
 It's too dangerous 
without a Labor...

1104
01:18:10,539 --> 01:18:12,449
 ...and DELICATE 
decision-making might be needed.

1105
01:18:12,449 --> 01:18:13,750
 Ohta CAN'T handle it !

1106
01:18:13,750 --> 01:18:15,349
 WHAT ?!

1107
01:18:15,349 --> 01:18:16,349
 Go !

1108
01:18:16,349 --> 01:18:18,148
 I'll support you from here...

1109
01:18:21,250 --> 01:18:25,349
Forward and backup are 
two-in-one, right ?

1110
01:18:25,349 --> 01:18:26,449
And one more thing !

1111
01:18:26,449 --> 01:18:29,349
We don't have much time, so we'll proceed 
with the original plan at the same time !

1112
01:18:29,349 --> 01:18:30,648
 WHAT ?!

1113
01:18:38,648 --> 01:18:40,559
I heard HOS's true 
nature was confirmed.

1114
01:18:40,559 --> 01:18:43,159
Oh,
 Chief Nagumo...

1115
01:18:43,159 --> 01:18:49,349
Yeah, we got a call from MIT saying 
that they'd finally dissected the file.

1116
01:18:49,349 --> 01:18:51,760
 So what's the verdict ?

1117
01:18:49,858 --> 01:18:51,760
 We hit the jackpot.

1118
01:18:51,760 --> 01:18:54,349
A virus was planted in HOS.

1119
01:18:54,349 --> 01:18:57,858
It invades the backup 
memory to start off...

1120
01:18:57,858 --> 01:19:02,769
...then it changes its name and gets 
into every available space possible.

1121
01:19:02,769 --> 01:19:07,568
There's no doubt that any computer that comes 
in contact with HOS will be contaminated.

1122
01:19:07,568 --> 01:19:10,068
By morning there's gonna 
be one hell of a mess...

1123
01:19:10,068 --> 01:19:15,068
MIT has already started programming a vaccine,
 but I wonder if it'll do the trick...

1124
01:19:15,068 --> 01:19:19,079
If only we'd known this half a day earlier,
 they wouldn't have had to go by themselves...

1125
01:19:19,079 --> 01:19:21,880
We can't even send 
in reinforcements...

1126
01:19:21,880 --> 01:19:25,479
But this did prove 
Goto's theory...

1127
01:19:25,479 --> 01:19:27,479
At least now we can 
arrange the rescue.

1128
01:19:27,479 --> 01:19:29,278
Wait a sec !

1129
01:19:29,278 --> 01:19:32,679
You said HOS or any computers that 
came in contact with it, right ?

1130
01:19:32,679 --> 01:19:37,699
What about the Ark's main computer?
 They're using it for the purge !!

1131
01:19:41,579 --> 01:19:47,988
 D level, block 5,
 30 seconds until purge.

1132
01:19:47,988 --> 01:19:57,099
 All personnel working in this 
block evacuate immediately.

1133
01:20:11,000 --> 01:20:15,099
D-5 block is purged.
 Alphonse is moving from D-7 to 9.

1134
01:20:15,099 --> 01:20:17,699
Get ready for the next one.
 Code for D-7 ?

1135
01:20:17,699 --> 01:20:20,300
FPD-00207.

1136
01:20:20,300 --> 01:20:24,699
Why can't we wait until she goes up to the next level,
 and then drop the entire floor ?

1137
01:20:24,699 --> 01:20:29,210
If the Ark loses too much weight at 
once it'll become dangerously unstable.

1138
01:20:29,210 --> 01:20:35,210
It's ok. If we drop the open blocks first,
 it should eliminate much of the resonance effect.

1139
01:20:35,210 --> 01:20:36,608
What's it like outside ?

1140
01:20:37,608 --> 01:20:39,309
Wind velocity 35...

1141
01:20:39,309 --> 01:20:41,108
...
now it's up to 36 !

1142
01:20:41,108 --> 01:20:42,809
D-7,
 here we go !

1143
01:20:42,809 --> 01:20:47,909
 D level,
 block 7 is purged.

1144
01:21:47,039 --> 01:21:49,229
Next !
 Code for E-2 !

1145
01:21:50,840 --> 01:21:53,539
As...Asuma !
 Look !

1146
01:21:53,539 --> 01:21:56,349
Blocks 3, 5 and 7 of D level,
 and all of C level !

1147
01:21:56,349 --> 01:21:59,449
They're flooded 
with runaway Labors !

1148
01:21:59,449 --> 01:22:00,550
What ?!

1149
01:22:00,550 --> 01:22:02,949
But the wind isn't over 
40m per second yet !

1150
01:22:02,949 --> 01:22:05,050
Either the simulation 
overlooked something...

1151
01:22:05,050 --> 01:22:08,449
...or the purging has 
worsened the effect !

1152
01:22:10,449 --> 01:22:15,050
Come on, you scrapheaps !
 I'll waste all of you !

1153
01:22:15,050 --> 01:22:16,050
 Hiromi !
 What's going on ?!

1154
01:22:16,050 --> 01:22:19,159
Runaway Labors are piling up 
at the other end of the bridge.

1155
01:22:19,159 --> 01:22:21,559
Ohta charged in just now.

1156
01:22:21,559 --> 01:22:22,648
What about Kanuka ?!

1157
01:22:22,648 --> 01:22:25,159
She left. She said she was 
gonna look for a weapon.

1158
01:22:25,159 --> 01:22:26,349
What do we do ?

1159
01:22:26,349 --> 01:22:30,349
Could it be that she's...

1160
01:22:39,559 --> 01:22:41,568
 Kanuka, don't !
 The Type-0 is too risky !

1161
01:22:41,568 --> 01:22:44,159
Don't worry, I'm using a system disk 
where the virus has been isolated.

1162
01:22:44,159 --> 01:22:47,068
Assuming all goes well I 
should be able to control it.

1163
01:22:47,068 --> 01:22:48,769
 But what if the virus 
has hidden somewhere...

1164
01:22:48,769 --> 01:22:51,159
Then this Labor will be a 
threat whether I use it or not !

1165
01:22:51,159 --> 01:22:54,369
Besides, Ohta won't be able to 
hold them all off on his own.

1166
01:22:54,369 --> 01:22:57,369
I'm willing to take the gamble.
 Clancy out !

1167
01:23:14,579 --> 01:23:17,579
 Noa ! Can you hear me ?!
 The situation's changed !

1168
01:23:17,579 --> 01:23:20,579
 The runaways have started 
earlier than estimated !

1169
01:23:20,579 --> 01:23:22,778
 We don't have much time left,
 so proceed at full speed !

1170
01:23:22,778 --> 01:23:23,579
 That's all !

1171
01:23:23,579 --> 01:23:25,188
Thanks for telling me...

1172
01:24:53,608 --> 01:24:54,630
Birds ?

1173
01:25:21,539 --> 01:25:24,340
The wind velocity outside 
is now over 40m per second !

1174
01:25:24,340 --> 01:25:25,438
We can't wait any longer !

1175
01:25:25,438 --> 01:25:27,738
Noa ! Answer me !
 Noa !

1176
01:25:27,738 --> 01:25:30,639
 The ID's around 
a raven's leg...

1177
01:25:30,639 --> 01:25:32,639
Just report your conclusions !

1178
01:25:32,639 --> 01:25:34,039
Is there anybody up there ?!

1179
01:25:34,039 --> 01:25:37,840
 No !
 Nobody's here !

1180
01:25:44,050 --> 01:25:46,949
It's not accepting any input...

1181
01:25:46,949 --> 01:25:50,148
The main computer was 
contaminated too ?!

1182
01:25:50,148 --> 01:25:54,648
 Control room,
 please respond !

1183
01:25:54,648 --> 01:25:57,148
 Runaway Labors are increasing !

1184
01:25:57,148 --> 01:25:59,250
There's so many of them...

1185
01:25:59,250 --> 01:26:01,760
I can't hold them off if they 
start crossing the bridge !

1186
01:26:01,760 --> 01:26:04,648
Please hurry up 
with that purge !

1187
01:26:08,159 --> 01:26:09,559
 There's gotta be something...

1188
01:26:09,559 --> 01:26:11,559
 ...some way...

1189
01:26:14,858 --> 01:26:16,648
There should be a backup 
manual ignition system...

1190
01:26:16,648 --> 01:26:21,760
...something that blows away all the 
block joints without the computer relay !

1191
01:26:23,470 --> 01:26:26,970
But how do we get to the ignition 
point while we're stuck in this mess ?!

1192
01:26:26,970 --> 01:26:28,269
Just deal with it !

1193
01:26:34,269 --> 01:26:38,659
The top level of the main shaft,
 right under subcontrol...

1194
01:26:38,659 --> 01:26:41,568
Good thing the police stress 
the value of human life.

1195
01:26:41,568 --> 01:26:44,159
Bingo,
 and just in time !

1196
01:26:44,159 --> 01:26:45,880
It's right under Noa's feet !

1197
01:26:48,179 --> 01:26:50,679
Take that !

1198
01:27:19,188 --> 01:27:20,590
The Type-0 ?!

1199
01:27:33,398 --> 01:27:34,398
My God...!

1200
01:27:44,599 --> 01:27:46,699
 Ohta !
 Kanuka !

1201
01:27:46,699 --> 01:27:49,099
 We're gonna start 
purging the entire floor !

1202
01:27:49,099 --> 01:27:50,898
 Get back to the 
command center !

1203
01:27:50,898 --> 01:27:53,210
 Ohta !

